article.headline: Maryland 67, American U. 51
article.story: COLLEGE PARK, Md. -- Landon Milbourne and David Neal each scored 14 points, and Maryland avenged an embarrassing loss to American University with a 67-51 victory Monday night. Greivis Vasquez scored 13 for the Terrapins (8-2), who have won four straight since successive losses last month against Top 25 foes Gonzaga and Georgetown. Last year, the Eagles stunned Maryland on its home floor 67-59. Determined to avoid anything resembling a repeat performance, Maryland bolted to a 9-0 lead and never let the margin shrink below six points. Derrick Mercer scored 12 points and Garrison Carr had 11 for American (5-6). Coming off a 34-point performance at Maryland-Baltimore County in which he made eight 3-pointers, Carr went 1-for-6 from beyond the arc against the Terrapins.
